Wiper is wooing Machakos Deputy Governor Bernard Kiala to take up the position of county assembly speaker after he lost to Wavinya Ndeti in the governor nominations.Speaking during a leaders&rsquo; meeting at Machakos Golf Club on Friday, Makueni Senator Mutula Kilonzo Jr said party leader Kalonzo Musyoka had asked him to reach out to Kiala.&ldquo;The Wiper Party leader sent me to talk to Kiala and I want to say it here that I have already met him and he has agreed to work with Wavinya and [her running mate Peter] Mathuki. And since we do not want his cup empty, Wiper will propose him to be the speaker to the assembly,&rdquo; he said.Party leader Kalonzo Musyoka confirmed that he asked Kilonzo to reach out to Kiala, and added that it was an honour that Kiala had agreed to be part of the team.&ldquo;I want to thank Senator Junior for reaching out to Kiala and producing some good results. I had personally tried to talk to Kiala but he would not listen to me,&rdquo; he said.Ndeti said she is ready to work with Kiala.However, Kiala told the Star on the phone yesterday that he would respond to the allegations today.He said he was to meet Kilonzo in Nairobi yesterday.&ldquo;I do not have an answer to that question right now but tomorrow [Monday] I will be able to say something. Senator Mutula has just called me and asked me to meet him in Nairobi today [Sunday] to discuss some serious issues,&rdquo; Kiala said.